  "prompt": "Will I pass a drug test in 2 weeks as a non regular smoker?",
  "response": "Whether you'll pass a drug test in two weeks as a non-regular smoker depends on several factors, including how much and how recently you\u2019ve used cannabis, your body composition, metabolism, and the type of drug test being administered.\n\n### Key Points to Consider:\n1. **Usage Details**:\n   - How much cannabis did you consume? Higher amounts take longer to clear.\n   - How recently did you last use it? The more time that passes, the better your chances of passing.\n\n2. **Metabolism and Body Fat**:\n   - THC is fat-soluble, so individuals with higher body fat may retain it longer.\n   - Faster metabolisms clear THC more quickly.\n\n3. **Type of Test**:\n   - **Urine Test**: THC metabolites can typically be detected for 3\u201330 days after use, depending on frequency and amount. As a non-regular smoker, it\u2019s likely to clear within 1\u20132 weeks, but it\u2019s not guaranteed.\n   - **Blood Test**: THC is detectable for 1\u20132 days in occasional users.\n   - **Saliva Test**: THC is detectable for 1\u20133 days in most cases.\n   - **Hair Test**: THC can be detected for up to 90 days, but this is less common.\n\n### General Timeline for Occasional Smokers:\n- If you\u2019ve only used cannabis once or twice, THC metabolites may clear within **3\u20137 days**.\n- If you\u2019ve smoked a moderate amount in the past few weeks, it could take **7\u201314 days** to clear.\n\n### How to Improve Your Chances:\n- **Hydrate**: Drink plenty of water to help flush out toxins.\n- **Exercise**: Moderate exercise can help burn fat where THC is stored, but avoid intense exercise a few days before the test, as it can release stored THC into your system.\n- **Healthy Diet**: Eat foods that support liver detoxification (e.g., fiber, vegetables).\n- **Avoid More Use**: Stop using cannabis immediately to give your body time to clear it.\n\n### The Bottom Line:\nIf you\u2019re a non-regular smoker and haven\u2019t used cannabis recently or in large amounts, there\u2019s a good chance you\u2019ll pass a urine test in two weeks. However, there\u2019s no absolute guarantee, as individual factors vary. For more certainty, consider using an at-home drug test kit to check your status before the official test.",
